ing: 1 (28 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chile peppers
2 (14 ounce) cans kidney beans, rinsed and drained
2 (14.5 ounce) cans pinto beans, rinsed and drained
des: "This is a chili I have been making for years. I have made it with all kinds of ground meats (beef, turkey, deer, elk) but I prefer ground moose. The longer you let it simmer the better as the flavors will blend. Top with shredded cheddar cheese. Serve with fresh baked cornbread and sweet honey butter. Men LOVE this meal!"
ins:
Brown the ground moose in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Combine the moose, diced tomatoes, chili beans, kidney beans, pinto beans, olives, onion, and bell pepper in a slow cooker; stir in the chili seasoning. Set the slow cooker to Low; cook 8 to 12 hours.
